bug: 'for' expression can't be invoked with square brackets

It seems that when we capture a 'for' expression as an iterator
record, we can't invoke it with square brackets.  I consider this a
bug, as the square bracket loop is meant to result in parallel
execution if possible, and to fall back to serial execution otherwise.
I have a feeling that there's nothing deep going on here, simply a
path through our execution that hasn't ever been plumbed through.
